equation_narrative.headline: Aromatic core position resolved through structural contacts and late F-specific channels
equation_narrative.story: Position 4 in ubiquitin sits in a hydrophobic core environment with 8 structural contacts. Early layers (1-23) assemble a representation reflecting this buried, hydrophobic context—the logit lens shows fluctuating support for various hydrophobic and polar residues (S, L, A, V, K) as the model reads structural neighbors and builds abstract features. The representation remains chemically ambiguous through L23, with no clear aromatic signal despite F being the answer. The decision crystallizes in layers 24-33: F-specific prediction channels activate at L25 (F rises from 8.5% to 14.3%), and massive MLP support arrives at L30-31 (neurons N30:1839 and N30:4211 contribute +3.08 combined). F reaches 97.9% by L33, with Y as distant runner-up at 1.35%.

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 gather structural and local context without committing to an aromatic residue. The model reads 8 structural contacts through attention heads, building a representation consistent with buried hydrophobic positions. Early logit-lens leaders include S (22.6% at L0), L (17% at L4), and A (21.2% at L5), reflecting the hydrophobic character of the local environment rather than aromatic specificity. Mid-layer features like F18:7701 (18.3 proj) and F18:5480 (15.2 proj) encode abstract structural properties. The representation oscillates between hydrophobic (L, V, A) and charged (K) character through L23, with F remaining below 10% until the decision phase begins. Only 2 co-evolving positions provide signal, suggesting this position is primarily constrained by local structure rather than long-range functional coupling.
perception_phase.context_character: Buried hydrophobic core environment with strong structural constraints from 8 nearby contacts. The representation through L23 is hydrophobic-leaning but chemically ambiguous, lacking clear aromatic specificity despite the local packing requirements.
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: 8 residues within contact distance, read primarily through attention in layers 9-18
Co-evolutionary signal: minimal (only 2 coupled positions), indicating local structural constraints dominate
L9 attention features: F9:5728 (49.6 proj), F9:1281 (45.3 proj) encode structural context
L18 features: F18:7701 (18.3 proj), F18:5063 (15.3 proj) refine buried position representation
Local sequence: MQI[F]VKT context provides hydrophobic neighbors at positions 3 (I) and 5 (V)

decision_phase.summary: The decision crystallizes at L25 when F first takes the lead (14.3%), though competition continues through L27. Massive MLP support arrives at L30-31: N30:1839 contributes +1.88 toward F (the single strongest neuron vote in the entire forward pass), and N30:4211 adds +1.20. Late attention features F30:2305 (56.2 proj) and F33:8134 (119.9 proj, MLP-sourced) act as high-confidence F-specific prediction channels. F surges from 41.2% at L29 to 97.9% at L33, decisively outcompeting Y (1.35%) and L (0.49%).
decision_phase.transition: The L23-25 boundary marks the shift from context assembly to amino-acid-specific prediction. At L23, F sits at only 8.5% with V leading at 21.2%. By L25, F reaches 14.3% and takes the lead for the first time, driven by MLP neurons (N25:1416 contributes +0.33, N25:1854 adds +0.28). This is when the representation transitions from encoding 'buried hydrophobic position' to actively predicting 'phenylalanine specifically.'

candidates.narrative: F emerges late and decisively. It remains below 10% through L23, then activates F-specific prediction machinery at L25 (rises to 14.3%). The critical surge occurs at L30-31: neuron N30:1839 delivers +1.88 projection (the strongest single vote), N30:4211 adds +1.20, and attention feature F30:2305 contributes 56.2 proj. Final MLP feature F33:8134 (119.9 proj) and F33:6738 (106.9 proj) seal the prediction at 97.9%. The late activation reflects the model's need to integrate structural burial with aromatic-specific packing requirements.
candidates.key_layers: Emerges at L25 (14.3%), dominant by L30 (68.9%), final confidence 97.9% at L33
key_evidence: N30:1839 (MLP, +1.88 proj) — strongest single neuron vote for F
F33:8134 (MLP, 119.9 proj) — final high-confidence F feature

candidates.narrative: Y peaks early at 12% (L1) when the representation is still chemically unrefined, then fades as F-specific features activate. Y shares aromatic character with F but lacks the pure hydrophobic bulk. It receives modest support from N29:2192 (+0.46 proj, though this neuron votes even more strongly for Y at +0.95), but cannot compete with the massive F-specific MLP support at L30-31. Y finishes at 1.35%, the only other aromatic candidate to remain viable.
candidates.key_layers: Peaks at L1 (12%), fades through decision phase, final 1.35%
key_evidence: Early logit-lens prominence reflects aromatic-compatible representation
N29:2192 provides +0.46 toward Y (but +0.95 toward F)
Loses decisively to F's late MLP surge

candidates.narrative: L peaks at 17% (L4) when the representation is strongly hydrophobic-leaning, reflecting the buried core context and neighboring I/V residues. This is NOT the model predicting leucine—it's the logit lens projecting a representation that has accumulated hydrophobic structural signals. L fades as aromatic-specific features emerge in the decision phase, dropping to 0.49% by L33. The early prominence reflects context character (hydrophobic burial) rather than amino-acid-specific prediction.
candidates.key_layers: Peaks at L4 (17%), declines steadily, final 0.49%
key_evidence: Logit-lens peak reflects hydrophobic representation character, not prediction
Neighboring hydrophobic residues (I at pos 3, V at pos 5) contribute to early signal
Erased by aromatic-specific decision machinery after L24

candidates.narrative: S leads the logit lens at L0 (22.6%), the highest initial value for any candidate. This reflects the embedding-level representation before any contextual information is processed. S is polar and small, chemically incompatible with the buried hydrophobic core that emerges through structural attention. S drops rapidly as the model reads structural contacts (6.5% by L8, 0.09% by L33). The early prominence is an artifact of the initial embedding, not a meaningful prediction signal.
candidates.key_layers: Peaks at L0 (22.6%), erased by L8 (6.5%), final 0.09%
key_evidence: Highest logit-lens value at embedding layer (L0)
Incompatible with buried hydrophobic context assembled by L8
Rapidly suppressed as structural information flows in

candidates.narrative: V emerges in mid-layers (peaks at 23.4% at L15) as the representation encodes hydrophobic burial and beta-branched character. V is structurally similar to the neighboring residue at position 5 and compatible with core packing. It leads the logit lens at L21-25 (21-23%), representing the model's most refined hydrophobic representation before aromatic-specific features activate. V loses decisively when F-specific prediction channels fire at L25+, dropping to 7.7% by L29 and 0.03% by L33.
candidates.key_layers: Peaks at L15 (23.4%), leads L21-25, collapses after L25
key_evidence: Represents refined hydrophobic burial context in mid-layers
Neighboring V at position 5 contributes to representation character
Outcompeted by aromatic-specific machinery after L25

turning_points.description: The representation shifts from embedding-level ambiguity to hydrophobic-leaning as structural contacts are read. S drops from 22.6% to 6.5%, while hydrophobic candidates (L, A) rise. Attention heads begin reading the 8 structural contacts, establishing the buried core context. Features F1:5480 (45.0 proj) and F1:9146 (45.0 proj) encode early structural information. This is pure perception—the model is assembling a representation of the local environment, not yet predicting a specific amino acid.

The transition from perception to decision. At L23, the representation is hydrophobic but non-specific (V leads at 21.2%, F at only 8.5%). At L25, F-specific prediction machinery activates: MLP neurons N25:1416 (+0.33) and N25:1854 (+0.28) vote for F, and it takes the lead at 14.3%. This is the first moment the model commits to an aromatic residue. The representation shifts from 'buried hydrophobic position' to 'phenylalanine specifically.'

The decisive surge. F explodes from 41.2% (L29) to 68.9% (L30) to 85.3% (L31), driven by massive MLP support. N30:1839 contributes +1.88 (the single strongest neuron vote), N30:4211 adds +1.20, and attention feature F30:2305 delivers 56.2 proj. At L31, N31:1155 adds +1.53 and N31:358 contributes +0.93. This is where the model's confidence crystallizes—F becomes the overwhelming favorite, and Y/L are definitively eliminated.

deep_dives.label: Structural attention L1-9
deep_dives.caption: Early attention heads read the 8 structural contacts, establishing the buried hydrophobic core context. Look for heads with high structural_attn values in top_writing_events. This is where the representation shifts from embedding-level ambiguity to hydrophobic-leaning.

deep_dives.label: SAE features L9-18
deep_dives.caption: Mid-layer features encode abstract structural properties: burial, secondary structure preferences, and hydrophobic character. F9:5728 (49.6 proj) and F18:7701 (18.3 proj) are key. These features represent context, not predictions.

deep_dives.label: MLP transition L23-25
deep_dives.caption: The shift from perception to decision. At L23, MLP output is slightly negative (-1.13 total). At L24, it turns positive (+3.57). At L25, F-specific neurons activate (N25:1416, N25:1854) despite net negative MLP output (-6.56), showing the beginning of aromatic-specific prediction.

deep_dives.label: MLP decision L30-31
deep_dives.caption: The decisive MLP surge. N30:1839 (+1.88) and N30:4211 (+1.20) deliver the strongest F votes. At L31, N31:1155 (+1.53) and N31:358 (+0.93) continue the push. This is where F's probability explodes from 41% to 85%.

deep_dives.label: Final prediction features L33
deep_dives.caption: High-confidence F-specific features seal the prediction. F33:8134 (119.9 proj, MLP) and F33:6738 (106.9 proj, MLP) are the strongest. These are pure prediction channels with high F-specificity.

deep_dives.label: Velocity events L28-33
deep_dives.caption: Track the final acceleration toward F. L28 (+4.22 toward), L30 (+2.17 toward), L31 (+2.16 toward), L33 (+7.73 toward, driven by MLP -12.71 erasing competitors). The decision is made by L31; L32-33 are cleanup.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly predicts F by assembling a buried hydrophobic core context through structural attention (layers 1-23), then activating aromatic-specific prediction channels in the decision phase (layers 24-33). The strongest evidence comes from L30-31 MLP neurons: N30:1839 (+1.88) and N30:4211 (+1.20) deliver decisive F-specific votes, recognizing that this position requires not just hydrophobic burial but the specific pi-stacking and packing geometry of a large aromatic side chain. The late emergence of F (below 10% until L24) reflects the model's need to integrate multiple constraints—local hydrophobicity, structural burial, and aromatic-specific packing—before committing to the prediction.
